\section{NetworkUsageBlock}


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
This block contains the properties related to network usage. The block may be present several times to account for different types of network.


  		





  
  6
  
    

  		





  
  7
  
    
\begin{XMLexample}


  		





  
  8
  
    
<ur:NetworkUsageBlock>


  		





  
  9
  
    
<!â€” Network Usage properties go in here -->


  		





  
  10
  
    
</ur:NetworkUsageBlock>


  		





  
  11
  
    
\end{XMLexample}


  		





  
  12
  
    

  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14

  19
  
    
\subsection{NetworkClass}


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
The class of network used. This is a descriptive value, which allows the network system to provide details about the network used. The \emph{NetworkResourceBandwidth} attribute represent the maximum bandwidth allowed for this \emph{NetworkClass} expressed in bytes.


  		





  
  22
  
    

  		





  
  23
  
    
\begin{itemize}


  		





  
  24
  
    
\item \emph{NetworkClass} MUST be present in the \emph{NetworkUsageBlock}.


  		





  
  25
  
    
\item The \emph{NetworkClass} field type MUST be a string.


  		





  
  26
  
    
\item The value ``Ethernet'' MUST be supported.


  		





  
  27
  
    
\item The \emph{NetworkResourceBandwidth} attribute field type MUST be a positive Integer.


  		





  
  28
  
    
\end{itemize}


  		





  
  29
  
    

  		





  
  30
  
    
\begin{XMLexample}


  		





  
  31
  
    
<ur:NetworkClass NetworkResourceBandwidth=100000000>"Ethernet"</ur:NetworkClass>


  		





  
  32
  
    
\end{XMLexample}


  		





  
  33
  
    

  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    

  		





  
  36
  
    
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\subsection{NetworkInboundUsed}


  		





  
  41
  
    

  		





  
  42
  
    
The number of physical bytes used on the network system for inbound network traffic.


  		





  
  43
  
    

  		





  
  44
  
    
\begin{itemize}


  		





  
  45
  
    
\item \emph{NetworkInboundUsed} MUST be present in the \emph{NetworkUsageBlock}.


  		





  
  46
  
    
\item The \emph{NetworkInboundUsed} attribute field type MUST be a positive Integer.


  		





  
  47
  
    
\end{itemize}


  		





  
  48
  
    

  		





  
  49
  
    
\begin{XMLexample}


  		





  
  50
  
    
<ur:NetworkInboundUsed>14728</ur:NetworkInboundUsed> 


  		





  
  51
  
    
\end{XMLexample}

\subsection{NetworkOutboundUsed}


  		





  
  60
  
    

  		





  
  61
  
    
The number of physical bytes used on the network system for outbound network traffic.


  		





  
  62
  
    

  		





  
  63
  
    
\begin{itemize}


  		





  
  64
  
    
\item \emph{NetworkOutboundUsed} MUST be present in the \emph{NetworkUsageBlock}.


  		





  
  65
  
    
\item The \emph{NetworkOutboundUsed} attribute field type MUST be a positive Integer.


  		





  
  66
  
    
\end{itemize}


  		





  
  67
  
    

  		





  
  68
  
    
\begin{XMLexample}

<ur:NetworkOutboundUsed>14728</ur:NetworkOutboundUsed>
